97
00:10:16,767 --> 00:10:19,600
But maybe it's better this way.

98
00:10:20,467 --> 00:10:21,433
Satomi?

99
00:10:22,700 --> 00:10:26,833
Because you're not giving up
on Irie at all.

100
00:10:33,733 --> 00:10:35,600
<i>You already know, don't you?</i>

101
00:10:36,700 --> 00:10:41,067
<i>Even if there's a rival or any obstacles,</i>

102
00:10:41,133 --> 00:10:43,700
<i>your feelings towards Irie won't change.</i>

103
00:10:45,233 --> 00:10:48,467
<i>If that's the case,</i>
<i>Kin-chan should give up on you</i>

104
00:10:48,533 --> 00:10:50,133
<i>and move forward.</i>

105
00:10:57,500 --> 00:11:03,000
But I haven't
gotten Irie's attention either.

106
00:11:10,567 --> 00:11:11,633
<i>Speak of the devil...</i>

107
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:23,767
Irie, why don't we go to a movie
this Sunday?

108
00:11:23,833 --> 00:11:25,100
I have two tickets.

109
00:11:26,467 --> 00:11:32,833
<i>What? Yuko Matsumoto is also aiming</i>
<i>to have a first date with Irie?</i>

110
00:11:33,833 --> 00:11:37,233
<i>Oh, no. I don't feel like I can win.</i>

111
00:11:46,967 --> 00:11:51,267
-What are you doing, Mr. Sudo?
-Why are you here, Aihara?

112
00:11:53,867 --> 00:11:56,200
You were watching Irie, weren't you?

113
00:11:56,267 --> 00:11:59,900
Are you watching Ms. Matsumoto,
as well?

114
00:12:02,467 --> 00:12:07,833
Maybe Ms. Matsumoto is who you admire.

115
00:12:10,667 --> 00:12:12,200
-Aihara.
-No!

116
00:12:12,267 --> 00:12:14,000
What are you doing in broad daylight?

117
00:12:16,800 --> 00:12:19,767
