This is... well...

118
00:12:19,833 --> 00:12:24,233
-The rumor I heard was true.
-The rumor?

119
00:12:24,967 --> 00:12:27,633
The rumor that you and Mr. Sudo
have something going on.

120
00:12:29,667 --> 00:12:31,633
Don't make up stories.

121
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:35,367
Because you told people
that you'd give up on Irie.

122
00:12:35,433 --> 00:12:38,033
That's because of Mr. Sudo, right?

123
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:40,667
-It's a big rumor in the club.
-What?

124
00:12:41,233 --> 00:12:43,533
-Is that right?
-No, that's not true.

125
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:46,167
Irie, there's a misunderstanding.

126
00:12:46,233 --> 00:12:48,400
-It's not that.
-It's none of my business.

127
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:57,167
Oh, Matsumoto.
In answer to your invitation...

128
00:12:58,267 --> 00:13:01,133
I'm free on Sunday,
so, I can go to a movie.

129
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:03,267
Really? Thank you.

130
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:24,300
It's your fault.
You put your weight on me all of a sudden.

131
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:28,467
I forgot that you injured your ankle.
I'm very sorry.

132
00:13:32,100 --> 00:13:34,800
I didn't know that our relationship

133
00:13:34,867 --> 00:13:37,267
was a big piece of gossip
in the Tennis Club.

134
00:13:38,633 --> 00:13:40,267
There's no way that's happening.

135
00:13:41,833 --> 00:13:43,833
It's just Ms. Matsumoto's made-up story.

136
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:46,267
So that she can give Irie
a good impression of her.

137
00:13:47,033 --> 00:13:50,433
Matsumoto is not the kind of girl
who tells a stupid lie like that.

138
00:13:54,533 --> 00:13:58,633
You really like Matsumoto, don't you?

139
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:03,967
Aihara, I want to discuss something
with you.

140
00:14:08,133 --> 00:14:09,167
Well, say...

141
00:14:09,900 --> 00:14:14,600
you like Irie and I like Matsumoto.

142
00:14:14,667 --> 00:14:18,033
Matsumoto likes Irie. Isn't that bad?

143
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:20,633
Nobody can be happy, right?

144
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:23,467
So, I suggest that we come up
with an agreement

145
00:14:23,533 --> 00:14:26,033
and cooperate with each other.
How about that?

146
00:14:26,100 --> 00:14:29,133
-Cooperate. How?
-For example...

147
00:14:33,767 --> 00:14:34,600
What?

148
00:14:36,933 --> 00:14:40,700
-Really?
-Tail Irie during his date?

149
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:43,800
What will you do if Kin-chan hears us?

150
00:14:44,467 --> 00:14:47,833
Good. Kin-chan seems to be off today.

151
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:52,067
What's wrong, Kotoko?

152
00:14:53,133 --> 00:14:55,267
Tissue, tissue. Good.

153
00:14:55,900 --> 00:14:59,033
-Okay. It's done.
-What would you do tailing him?

154
00:15:00,267 --> 00:15:01,767
I don't know, but...

155
00:15:02,633 --> 00:15:05,467
I don't know what to do
if anything happens with those two.

156
00:15:07,300 --> 00:15:11,367
Thinking of that makes me worry so much.

157
00:15:12,300 --> 00:15:15,300
-You're so pitiful.
-I can't help it.

158
00:15:15,367 --> 00:15:19,600
You just got robbed of your first date
by Yuko Matsumoto.

159
00:15:19,667 --> 00:15:22,167
On top of all that,
you're going to tail him?

160
00:15:22,233 --> 00:15:25,233
That's just like Mr. Sudo and you
are going out on a date.

161
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:28,567
Don't you hear a weird noise?

162
00:15:29,367 --> 00:15:32,400
Jinko, we're talking
about important stuff.

163
00:15:32,467 --> 00:15:33,800
Zip your mouth.

164
00:15:38,233 --> 00:15:40,933
-Do you want this apple tea?
-Orange juice.

165
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:48,633
Mr. Sudo and Kotoko are going on a date?
What's happening?

166
00:15:51,667 --> 00:15:54,467
<i>Are you sure</i>
<i>that's what you're going to do?</i>

167
00:15:55,900 --> 00:15:59,233
<i>I can't do anything about it.</i>
<i>That's what love is.</i>

168
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:04,567
Did Kotoko fall for a new guy?

169
00:16:05,567 --> 00:16:08,033
That mustache dude?

170
00:16:10,433 --> 00:16:14,500
<i>-The date is... a movie.</i>
<i>-Ginza.</i>

171
00:16:15,467 --> 00:16:18,767
<i>-Oh, Karasumori?</i>
<i>-Shinbashi.</i>

172
00:16:20,700 --> 00:16:23,167
Ginza, Karasumori.

173
00:16:23,767 --> 00:16:27,300
-Shinbashi.
-I don't care about the place.

174
00:16:29,700 --> 00:16:32,167
<i>The movie date... Roman...</i>

175
00:16:39,867 --> 00:16:42,467
Date, movie.

176
00:16:43,333 --> 00:16:46,267
Ginza, Karasumori.

177
00:16:47,133 --> 00:16:48,333
Shinbashi.

178
00:16:50,367 --> 00:16:51,233
Roman?

179
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:14,333
"Date, movie, Ginza.

180
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:17,333
Karasumori, Shinbashi, Roman."

181
00:17:20,433 --> 00:17:24,833
I don't get it at all! I'm going crazy.

182
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:29,067
-Kinnosuke, what are you doing?
-I'm sorry, bro.

183
00:17:29,133 --> 00:17:29,967
What's that?

184
00:17:31,233 --> 00:17:33,700
-I don't get it.
-Is this some kind of code?

185
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:38,533
"Date, movie, Ginza, Karasumori.

186
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:42,133
-Shinbashi, Roman."
-It drives you crazy, doesn't it?

187
00:17:44,900 --> 00:17:45,933
I see.

188
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:50,600
-Did you figure it out?
-Are you going on a date?

189
00:17:50,667 --> 00:17:52,167
-No.
-That's what I thought.

190
00:17:52,833 --> 00:17:56,600
There's no way you could go out
on such a sexy grown-up date.

191
00:17:58,967 --> 00:18:03,400
What? What? What?

192
00:18:03,467 --> 00:18:04,500
Sexy?

193
00:18:08,300 --> 00:18:09,300
Sorry, Kotoko.

194
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:13,100
I went to many different Realtors,

195
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:18,567
but even when I found a good one,
somebody else won the contract by a hair.

196
00:18:19,767 --> 00:18:23,833
-I see.
-I'm so unlucky.

197
00:18:25,467 --> 00:18:28,933
Anyway, we won't be able
to find a new house anytime soon.

198
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:33,333
So, we'll have to live
with the Irie family for a while.

199
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:39,767
It's not something
that you have to apologize to me for.

200
00:18:40,467 --> 00:18:41,333
But...

201
00:18:42,567 --> 00:18:45,033
we made a big decision
to move out of the Iries' home.

202
00:18:46,433 --> 00:18:49,533
I'm wondering
if you were having a hard time.

203
00:18:53,633 --> 00:18:54,967
<i>In answer to your invitation,</i>

204
00:18:55,933 --> 00:18:58,600
I'm free on Sunday,
so, I can go to a movie.

205
00:18:58,667 --> 00:19:00,833
Really? Thank you.

206
00:19:08,433 --> 00:19:12,400
-I thought so.
-No, Dad.

207
00:19:14,267 --> 00:19:15,133
Listen.

208
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:23,433
I still like Irie.

209
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:29,533
-But Naoki's feelings are...
-That has nothing to do with it.

210
00:19:34,833 --> 00:19:39,400
It might be impossible for Irie
to fall for me, but...

211
00:19:42,867 --> 00:19:44,633
I don't want to give up until the end.

212
00:19:46,167 --> 00:19:50,600
You always tell me that it's not good
to quit in the middle of something.

213
00:19:52,967 --> 00:19:55,733
I realized after I left the Iries' home...

214
00:19:57,667 --> 00:20:02,700
something that I don't want to give up
is this feeling.

215
00:20:08,567 --> 00:20:11,200
So, don't worry about me anymore, Dad.

216
00:20:12,233 --> 00:20:13,867
Even if I get my heart broken,

217
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:17,300
it's better than doing nothing
and regretting it.

218
00:20:20,267 --> 00:20:23,367
-You're so similar.
-To my mom?

219
00:20:23,433 --> 00:20:25,967
No, to me.

220
00:20:28,033 --> 00:20:32,133
You are definitely my daughter.

221
00:20:39,433 --> 00:20:45,333
SUNDAY

222
00:20:50,167 --> 00:20:51,167
This isn't it.

223
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:00,533
The flower print isn't it either.

224
00:21:04,133 --> 00:21:06,133
White looks cute, too.

225
00:21:11,767 --> 00:21:12,900
I pick...

226
00:21:17,833 --> 00:21:18,667
this one.

227
00:21:43,433 --> 00:21:45,233
<i>Even if I put makeup on...</i>

228
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:49,667
<i>the person who's going on a date</i>
<i>with Irie is not me...</i>

229
00:21:51,133 --> 00:21:52,600
<i>but Matsumoto.</i>

230
00:22:08,933 --> 00:22:12,933
<i>I wanted to go on a date with Irie too.</i>

231
00:22:14,667 --> 00:22:17,567
<i>Get dressed up and put makeup on.</i>

232
00:22:18,367 --> 00:22:21,433
<i>We'd watch a movie and go shopping.</i>

233
00:22:23,567 --> 00:22:27,533
<i>Eat dinner at a fancy little restaurant.</i>

234
00:22:36,333 --> 00:22:37,267
All right.

235
00:22:55,667 --> 00:22:56,567
That's her.

236
00:23:17,833 --> 00:23:20,600
-Nice body.
-Mr. Sudo, when did you get here?

237
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:24,833
-Is Irie a quick worker?
-What?

238
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:27,600
Well, not so much.

239
00:23:27,667 --> 00:23:29,700
He's rather slow.

240
00:23:30,233 --> 00:23:32,100
That's because of you.

241
00:23:32,733 --> 00:23:35,267
Matsumoto's sexiness will tempt Irie.

242
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:41,467
Oh, Irie.

243
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:46,833
Irie.

244
00:23:47,767 --> 00:23:50,300
