-No, I came early.

245
00:23:51,033 --> 00:23:54,033
-You look good in that dress.
-Really?

246
00:23:54,733 --> 00:23:58,300
-I'm glad.
-That guy is being so affected.

247
00:23:59,467 --> 00:24:00,400
-Shall we go?
-Yes.

248
00:24:23,267 --> 00:24:25,300
Sexy... sexy...

249
00:24:25,933 --> 00:24:27,667
Hey, Kinnosuke, this way.

250
00:24:28,833 --> 00:24:29,867
Kotoko!

251
00:24:42,933 --> 00:24:45,133
I'd like to have seats right behind them.

252
00:24:47,333 --> 00:24:48,567
Hurry, hurry.

253
00:24:57,400 --> 00:25:00,600
Ta-da! See? Isn't it perfect?

254
00:25:01,233 --> 00:25:03,600
Movie, Shinbashi, Roman.

255
00:25:04,167 --> 00:25:06,200
A minute's walk from the Karasumori exit.

256
00:25:06,933 --> 00:25:08,167
How about Ginza?

257
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:10,467
You don't know that?

258
00:25:10,933 --> 00:25:13,367
When they feel naughty after the movie...

259
00:25:14,567 --> 00:25:17,400
they retire to a fancy little hotel
in Ginza.

260
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:25,867
That mustache guy, what is he thinking?

261
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:30,833
Showing something like this to Kotoko
and... doing something naughty?

262
00:25:46,633 --> 00:25:50,800
-Hey.
-I'm sorry.

263
00:25:50,867 --> 00:25:52,800
What are you doing? This way.

264
00:26:25,733 --> 00:26:26,867
What's this?

265
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:31,933
Oh, my. I... dropped a pamphlet.

266
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:34,867
Grandma, pull yourself together.

267
00:26:34,933 --> 00:26:37,133
You're right. Grandpa.

268
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:41,900
-Me, too.
-What are you doing?

269
00:26:41,967 --> 00:26:44,033
You got ketchup on your face.

270
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:46,967
Oh, my back.

271
00:26:53,067 --> 00:26:58,000
Hey, Kinnosuke, let's wait inside.

272
00:27:00,067 --> 00:27:01,733
I gave up on a kiss...

273
00:27:02,500 --> 00:27:05,800
but I'm never going to give up

274
00:27:05,867 --> 00:27:07,367
against other guys!

275
00:27:26,933 --> 00:27:28,600
Hey, what's wrong with you?

276
00:27:29,600 --> 00:27:31,433
Sit down. I can't see anything.

277
00:27:50,133 --> 00:27:53,667
-It was a good movie.
-Do you want to have some tea?

278
00:27:58,067 --> 00:27:58,900
Let's!

279
00:28:09,567 --> 00:28:13,267
I've been interested in you
since I was in junior high.

280
00:28:15,167 --> 00:28:17,933
I heard that there was
a prodigy tennis player in Tonan.

281
00:28:19,367 --> 00:28:22,300
On top of that, you're handsome
and have good grades.

282
00:28:22,367 --> 00:28:25,433
Your dad is CEO of a company
and a Tokyo University alumnus, right?

283
00:28:26,300 --> 00:28:28,467
I thought you'd apply for another college.

284
00:28:29,300 --> 00:28:32,433
But when I heard that you were going
to Tonan...

285
00:28:33,733 --> 00:28:34,800
I was happy.

286
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:37,633
I felt it was destiny.

287
00:28:39,567 --> 00:28:40,733
Is that right?

288
00:28:42,767 --> 00:28:47,767
Tell me, what type of girls do you like?

289
00:28:48,700 --> 00:28:49,633
My type?

290
00:28:51,333 --> 00:28:53,067
Let's see.

291
00:28:54,633 --> 00:28:58,433
Beautiful and... glamorous.

292
00:29:00,633 --> 00:29:02,133
I want a smart girl.

293
00:29:05,633 --> 00:29:07,833
And... being a good cook is a must.

294
00:29:10,700 --> 00:29:11,600
Aihara.

295
00:29:18,767 --> 00:29:20,933
There's something good about you.

296
00:29:22,267 --> 00:29:25,300
It's okay. You don't have to cheer me up.

297
00:29:27,633 --> 00:29:30,967
I see. What do you think?

298
00:29:32,033 --> 00:29:35,067
Don't we make a good couple?

299
00:29:37,433 --> 00:29:38,467
Probably.

300
00:29:44,100 --> 00:29:46,133
We still have time before dinner.

301
00:29:46,200 --> 00:29:48,767
-Will you go shopping with me?
-Sure.

302
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:56,800
Which one do you like?

303
00:29:58,767 --> 00:30:01,100
This one. You'll wear it well.

304
00:30:01,700 --> 00:30:02,567
Do you think so?

305
00:30:05,200 --> 00:30:07,900
Excuse me, may I try this on?

306
00:30:07,967 --> 00:30:10,600
Yes. Thank you. This way, please.

307
00:30:23,067 --> 00:30:27,200
How come Irie is looking
at women's accessories?

308
00:30:28,233 --> 00:30:30,767
Is he going to give it to Matsumoto?

309
00:30:31,367 --> 00:30:32,333
No way.

310
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:37,300
I've never gotten anything from him
even though I've been living with him.

311
00:30:41,600 --> 00:30:44,800
Irie, can you zip up the back?

312
00:30:57,967 --> 00:30:59,700
Thank you. How do I look?

313
00:30:59,767 --> 00:31:00,833
Mr. Sudo.

314
00:31:03,733 --> 00:31:04,600
Hold on.

315
00:31:07,100 --> 00:31:09,833
-What is he going to do?
-I'm scared.

316
00:31:13,367 --> 00:31:15,967
No, don't. Don't touch her.

317
00:31:16,033 --> 00:31:18,300
No!

318
00:31:20,033 --> 00:31:20,867
How about this?

319
00:31:21,700 --> 00:31:23,367
Nice, Irie.

320
00:31:24,033 --> 00:31:26,667
You have good taste.
It goes with this dress.

321
00:31:27,467 --> 00:31:28,933
Because the model is good.

322
00:31:30,533 --> 00:31:32,300
I'm happy to hear that
even if it's flattery.

323
00:31:33,633 --> 00:31:35,500
I feel dizzy with that different world.

324
00:31:38,367 --> 00:31:41,567
Don't you think
that they were made for each other?

325
00:31:42,467 --> 00:31:44,333
What are you doing, approving of them?

326
00:31:51,800 --> 00:31:53,833
-I'll hold it.
-Thank you.

327
00:32:02,067 --> 00:32:03,333
Okay, let's go.

328
00:32:05,467 --> 00:32:07,900
I want shoes, too.

329
00:32:08,900 --> 00:32:12,067
-I have a pair that I wanted.
-Watch out.

330
00:32:15,433 --> 00:32:16,300
Are you okay?

331
00:32:17,800 --> 00:32:20,967
-Thank you.
-It's good that you didn't get hurt.

332
00:32:31,667 --> 00:32:35,367
Mr. Sudo, I'm going home now.

333
00:32:35,867 --> 00:32:40,333
-What are you talking about?
-I can't bear to watch them anymore.

334
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:43,667
We're here to prevent the situation
that's unbearable to watch.

335
00:32:43,733 --> 00:32:47,967
But there's nothing we can do
if they like each other.

336
00:32:49,567 --> 00:32:51,033
It's too miserable.

337
00:32:53,100 --> 00:32:56,467
-I'm sorry, Mr. Sudo. I'm leaving.
-Okay.

338
00:32:56,533 --> 00:32:58,000
Get home safely.

339
00:32:59,367 --> 00:33:00,433
I'm sorry.

340
00:33:01,100 --> 00:33:02,800
What are you going to do with this?

341
00:33:03,967 --> 00:33:06,800
-I'll pay for the cleaning.
-That's not enough!

342
00:33:07,933 --> 00:33:10,933
This shirt is expensive. It's 100,000 yen!

343
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:12,100
100,000 yen?

344
00:33:12,733 --> 00:33:14,933
-What can I do?
-I'll take care of it.

345
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:17,567
-Here's 1020...
-Hey, lady.

346
00:33:18,367 --> 00:33:20,033
You have a pretty face.

347
00:33:20,100 --> 00:33:22,533
Why don't you come over to my office

348
00:33:22,600 --> 00:33:25,333
and discuss this and that? Let's go.

349
00:33:26,233 --> 00:33:27,067
Please, stop it.

350
00:33:27,133 --> 00:33:31,400
<i>I'm being punished</i>
<i>because I was interrupting someone's date.</i>

351
00:33:31,467 --> 00:33:34,133
-Let's go now.
-1500 yen should be enough.

352
00:33:38,067 --> 00:33:39,267
Why are you here?

353
00:33:40,467 --> 00:33:42,467
Hey, little fella, what did you just say?

354
00:33:43,333 --> 00:33:46,233
The cleaning fee
for the cheap shirt should be covered

355
00:33:46,300 --> 00:33:47,467
by 1500 yen.

356
00:33:48,133 --> 00:33:50,233
Don't be so arrogant.

357
00:33:58,867 --> 00:34:00,867
He's so cool, isn't he?

358
00:34:05,967 --> 00:34:08,367
Excuse me. Mr. Sudo.

359
00:34:10,967 --> 00:34:14,200
You got it now.
You've been tailing us for the whole day.

360
00:34:15,133 --> 00:34:18,900
Show her your strength
and get Matsumoto to fall for you.

361
00:34:28,100 --> 00:34:30,100
-Irie.
-Sorry, I've got to go now.

362
00:34:33,033 --> 00:34:36,033
-Wait!
-That's what I want to say!

363
00:34:37,133 --> 00:34:38,233
Take this!

364
00:34:57,300 --> 00:34:58,167
<i>I'm...</i>

365
00:35:00,833 --> 00:35:03,367
<i>running away with Irie.</i>

366
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:07,100
<i>It's like a dream.</i>

367
00:35:43,167 --> 00:35:44,100
<i>I wish...</i>

368
00:35:45,300 --> 00:35:48,067
<i>time would stop right now.</i>

369
00:36:08,300 --> 00:36:09,633
We'll be okay now.

370
00:36:30,133 --> 00:36:33,533
Irie, did you notice that...

371
00:36:34,400 --> 00:36:36,233
we were tailing you?

372
00:36:38,100 --> 00:36:42,633
I noticed your crappy tailing
when I got to the meeting place.

373
00:36:43,567 --> 00:36:46,367
Then you knew
that Mr. Sudo liked Matsumoto?

374
00:36:48,967 --> 00:36:52,600
I thought you and Sudo were a couple
until yesterday.

375
00:36:55,033 --> 00:36:57,533
But I knew when you two followed us.

376
00:37:00,633 --> 00:37:03,300
It was so funny to see your reaction.

377
00:37:05,767 --> 00:37:06,633
I'm sorry.

378
00:37:10,567 --> 00:37:13,267
When I heard you were going on a date
with Ms. Matsumoto...

379
00:37:13,867 --> 00:37:17,000
I couldn't contain myself.

380
00:37:18,667 --> 00:37:22,733
But if you like Ms. Matsumoto...

381
00:37:23,333 --> 00:37:26,267
-I got in your way so bad.
-Shall we go somewhere?

382
00:37:38,933 --> 00:37:39,767
Okay.

383
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:42,933
Then I'll go home.

384
00:37:47,167 --> 00:37:48,033
I'll go!

385
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:53,100
-Yes, yes, yes. I'm coming.
-Just say it once.

386
00:37:55,033 --> 00:37:56,100
I'm sorry.

387
00:37:58,767 --> 00:37:59,867
Where shall we go?

388
00:38:01,967 --> 00:38:03,300
Then a movie theater.

389
00:38:04,200 --> 00:38:07,100
We've been there, so...

390
00:38:07,167 --> 00:38:10,933
let's go shopping and after that
we'll go to a nice restaurant.

391
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:13,233
-We'll eat dinner, then...
-In that outfit?

392
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:19,000
You're right.

393
00:38:21,000 --> 00:38:24,300
You'll be embarrassed with me like this.

394
00:38:29,167 --> 00:38:30,000
Come on.

395
00:39:03,333 --> 00:39:07,933
It's so beautiful. Look, Irie.
Isn't it beautiful?

396
00:39:20,633 --> 00:39:21,600
Irie?

397
00:39:23,433 --> 00:39:26,667
Irie? Where are you?

398
00:39:32,667 --> 00:39:34,300
Irie.

399
00:39:36,133 --> 00:39:37,200
Irie.

400
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:18,633
<i>Is he making fun of me again?</i>

401
00:40:22,800 --> 00:40:26,433
We can't go to the restaurant like that.
Here's dinner.

402
00:40:46,067 --> 00:40:47,033
It's delicious.

403
00:40:48,633 --> 00:40:50,567
Anything tastes good when you're hungry.

404
00:40:56,500 --> 00:41:01,533
<i>No tasty French, Italian or Chinese...</i>

405
00:41:03,933 --> 00:41:06,067
<i>could win against this hamburger.</i>

406
00:41:31,967 --> 00:41:36,367
I'd never experienced anything hard
until a while ago.

407
00:41:39,333 --> 00:41:41,200
But since my last year of high school...

408
00:41:41,767 --> 00:41:44,033
after I got a love letter from you...

409
00:41:45,433 --> 00:41:48,667
almost every day has been a series
of hardships and frustrations.

410
00:41:53,567 --> 00:41:57,467
I think you're the trial that I was given.

411
00:41:59,133 --> 00:41:59,967
Trial?

412
00:42:01,967 --> 00:42:05,433
I... got confused by the first trial
that I was given.

413
00:42:06,600 --> 00:42:08,167
I was trying to get away from it.

414
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:11,133
You're telling me that I'm a pest
or something.

415
00:42:14,800 --> 00:42:15,667
But...

416
00:42:17,167 --> 00:42:19,100
compared to a life without any hardship,

417
00:42:19,567 --> 00:42:22,900
it's more interesting
to face these trials.

418
00:42:26,733 --> 00:42:27,567
Thank you.

419
00:42:38,100 --> 00:42:39,833
If you don't understand, it's okay.

420
00:42:41,100 --> 00:42:44,033
I can understand that.
Don't make a fool of me.

421
00:42:44,100 --> 00:42:49,033
You mean you wanted to get away from me,
but you changed your mind.

422
00:42:56,467 --> 00:42:59,133
Do you want to marry me?

423
00:42:59,200 --> 00:43:03,300
-Is this a proposal?
-Idiot. How can you think that?

424
00:43:05,800 --> 00:43:06,767
I'm saying that...

425
00:43:10,767 --> 00:43:14,633
I don't mind being in the same house
as you.

426
00:43:22,133 --> 00:43:23,233
That means...

427
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:28,033
you don't...

428
00:43:30,367 --> 00:43:31,900
hate me?

429
00:43:34,367 --> 00:43:37,967
You're hard to deal with,
but I don't hate you.

430
00:44:02,433 --> 00:44:05,233
Now not just your clothes
but your face will be a disaster.

431
00:44:07,233 --> 00:44:08,200
I can't help it.

432
00:45:27,733 --> 00:45:29,100
It was a good one.

433
00:45:30,000 --> 00:45:31,967
Three movies in a row is something else.

434
00:45:34,267 --> 00:45:37,167
Oh, Kinnosuke, are you still here?

435
00:45:39,567 --> 00:45:42,700
Kotoko, where are you?

436
00:45:44,833 --> 00:45:45,667
Kinnosuke?

437
00:45:48,400 --> 00:45:49,233
Kinnosuke?

438
00:45:53,067 --> 00:45:54,100
It's bad.

439
00:46:10,167 --> 00:46:15,133
<i>After an unexpected turn of events,</i>
<i>I won my first date with Irie.</i>

440
00:46:16,333 --> 00:46:19,333
<i>It was completely different</i>
<i>from what I had dreamed of, but...</i>

441
00:46:22,367 --> 00:46:25,900
<i>more than our first kiss...</i>

442
00:46:26,933 --> 00:46:29,267
<i>or the first time he held me...</i>

443
00:46:30,533 --> 00:46:33,833
<i>I felt Irie...</i>

444
00:46:34,433 --> 00:46:36,700
<i>was even closer to me.</i>

445
00:46:56,600 --> 00:46:59,033
No, I'm against that.

446
00:47:03,500 --> 00:47:07,400
Just when Kotoko finally came back,
you're moving out?

447
00:47:10,533 --> 00:47:14,600
Well, boys need that kind of experience.

448
00:47:15,733 --> 00:47:17,233
If Naoki wants to do it...

449
00:47:18,033 --> 00:47:21,367
it may not be a bad idea
for him to live by himself.

450
00:47:23,900 --> 00:47:24,867
Why don't you try it?

451
00:47:27,100 --> 00:47:28,167
Thank you.

452
00:47:37,900 --> 00:47:41,433
<i>Irie is moving out of here</i>
<i>and living by himself?</i>

453
00:47:43,067 --> 00:47:47,167
<i>He just told me</i>
<i>that he didn't mind living with me.</i>

454
00:47:48,400 --> 00:47:49,533
<i>Why?</i>

455
00:47:51,800 --> 00:47:53,067
<i>What does this mean?</i>

456
00:49:30,800 --> 00:49:33,133
I wonder if he doesn't like me.

457
00:49:33,400 --> 00:49:36,600
Since he moved out as
soon as we're back.

458
00:49:36,800 --> 00:49:40,967
I found out. Why don't we go spy
on him where he works?

459
00:49:41,267 --> 00:49:44,500
I'll work here. That way I can be
close to Irie.

460
00:49:44,733 --> 00:49:46,167
-Thank you for waiting.
-Yeah.

461
00:49:46,367 --> 00:49:50,567
Ms. Matsumoto, how do you know
that Irie works here?

462
00:49:50,800 --> 00:49:55,767
-He told me.
-I'll stay with you right here.

463
00:49:55,967 --> 00:49:59,133
{\an8}The distance between Irie and me
will get farther and farther.

464
00:49:59,200 --> 00:50:00,467
{\an8}DISCLAIMER:
THIS DRAMA IS A WORK OF FICTION

